== Overview == === Ancestry === According to the {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|12=draft}}, Ankoku-no-Miyatsuko's ancestor was {{ill|Mizunohowake no Mikoto|ja|水之穂真若王|12=draft}}, a son of {{ill|Hikoimasu no Mikoto|ja|日子坐王|12=draft}}, and is thus considered related to the {{ill|Ōmi-no-Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|淡海国造|12=draft}}.
=== Clan === The Ankoku-no-Miyatsuko belonged to the '''{{ill|Yasu clan|ja|安氏|12=draft}}''' (Yasu-uji), whose {{ill|Kabane|ja|カバネ|12=draft}} was '''{{ill|Ason|ja|直 (姓)|12=draft}}'''.
=== Base of Operations === The Ankoku-no-Miyatsuko governed from {{ill|Yasu District|ja|野洲郡|12=draft}} in Ōmi Province, corresponding to modern {{ill|Yasu|ja|野洲市|12=draft}} and {{ill|Moriyama|ja|守山市|12=draft}} in {{ill|Shiga Prefecture|ja|滋賀県|12=draft}}. Some sources suggest they later came under the control of the {{ill|Ōmi-no-Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|淡海国造|12=draft}} [citation needed].
=== Clan Deity === The clan's {{ill|Ujigami|ja|氏神|12=draft}} is unknown, but {{ill|Ame-no-Mikage-no-Kami|ja|天之御影神|12=draft}} has been suggested.<ref>Kenji Kawaguchi, *Tokyo Bijutsu Selection 23: Continuation of the Genealogies of the Gods* (Tokyo Bijutsu, 1980), p. 66.</ref>
=== Notable Figures === * '''Ōtamusaka no Mikoto''' (大多牟坂王, also known as Ōtamuya Wake or Ōtamuwake) ** The first Ankoku-no-Miyatsuko of Ōmi. He was a third-generation descendant of {{ill|Hikoimasu no Mikoto|ja|彦坐王|12=draft}} or a descendant of {{ill|Amatsuhikone|ja|天津彦根命|12=draft}}. * '''Futaji Hime''' (布多遅比売, also known as Ryōdōiri Hime) ** Daughter of Ōtamusaka no Mikoto. She married {{ill|Yamato Takeru|ja|倭建命|12=draft}} and bore {{ill|Inaiwawake no Mikoto|ja|稲依別王|12=draft}}. * '''Sakata Tarine no Kimi''' (坂田垂根君) ** Son of Ōtamusaka no Mikoto. == See Also == * {{ill|List of Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|国造の一覧|12=draft}}
