=== Notable Figures === * '''Ōtamusaka no Mikoto''' (大多牟坂王, also known as Ōtamuya Wake or Ōtamuwake) ** The first Ankoku-no-Miyatsuko of Ōmi. He was a third-generation descendant of {{ill|Hikoimasu no Ōkimi|lt=Hikoimasu no Ōkimi|lt=Hikoimasu no Mikoto|ja|彦坐王|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikoimasu no Mikoto|qq=}} or a descendant of {{ill|Amatsuhikone|ja|天津彦根命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amatsuhikone|qq=}}. * '''Futaji Hime''' (布多遅比売, also known as Ryōdōiri Hime) ** Daughter of Ōtamusaka no Mikoto. She married {{ill|Yamato Takeru|ja|倭建命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Takeru|qq=}} and bore {{ill|Inaiwawake no Mikoto|ja|稲依別王|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Inaiwawake no Mikoto|qq=}}. * '''Sakata Tarine no Kimi''' (坂田垂根君) ** Son of Ōtamusaka no Mikoto. == See Also == * {{ill|List of Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|国造の一覧|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/List of Kuni no Miyatsuko|qq=}}
