== Overview == === Ancestry === According to the [[:en:Kojiki|Kojiki]], Ankoku-no-Miyatsuko's ancestor was {{ill|Mizunohowake no Mikoto|ja|水之穂真若王|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mizunohowake no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, a son of {{ill|Hikoimasu no Ōkimi|lt=Hikoimasu no Ōkimi|lt=Hikoimasu no Mikoto|ja|日子坐王|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikoimasu no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 彦坐王}}, and is thus considered related to the {{ill|Ōmi-no-Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|淡海国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmi-no-Kuni no Miyatsuko|qq=}}.
=== Clan === The Ankoku-no-Miyatsuko belonged to the '''{{ill|Yasu clan|ja|安氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yasu clan|qq=}}''' (Yasu-uji), whose [[:en:Kabane|Kabane]] was '''{{ill|Ason|ja|直 (姓)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ason|qq=}}'''.
=== Base of Operations === The Ankoku-no-Miyatsuko governed from [[:en:Yasu District, Shiga|Yasu District]] in Ōmi Province, corresponding to modern [[:en:Yasu, Shiga|Yasu]] and [[:en:Moriyama, Shiga|Moriyama]] in [[:en:Shiga Prefecture|Shiga Prefecture]]. Some sources suggest they later came under the control of the {{ill|Ōmi-no-Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|淡海国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmi-no-Kuni no Miyatsuko|qq=}} [citation needed].
=== Clan Deity === The clan's [[:en:Ujigami|Ujigami]] is unknown, but {{ill|Ame-no-Mikage-no-Kami|ja|天之御影神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ame-no-Mikage-no-Kami|qq=}} has been suggested.<ref>Kenji Kawaguchi, *Tokyo Bijutsu Selection 23: Continuation of the Genealogies of the Gods* (Tokyo Bijutsu, 1980), p. 66.</ref>
=== Notable Figures === * '''Ōtamusaka no Mikoto''' (大多牟坂王, also known as Ōtamuya Wake or Ōtamuwake) ** The first Ankoku-no-Miyatsuko of Ōmi. He was a third-generation descendant of {{ill|Hikoimasu no Ōkimi|lt=Hikoimasu no Ōkimi|lt=Hikoimasu no Mikoto|ja|彦坐王|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikoimasu no Mikoto|qq=}} or a descendant of {{ill|Amatsuhikone|ja|天津彦根命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amatsuhikone|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to アマツヒコネ}}. * '''Futaji Hime''' (布多遅比売, also known as Ryōdōiri Hime) ** Daughter of Ōtamusaka no Mikoto. She married {{ill|Yamato Takeru|ja|倭建命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Takeru|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ヤマトタケル}} and bore {{ill|Inaiwawake no Mikoto|ja|稲依別王|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Inaiwawake no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. * '''Sakata Tarine no Kimi''' (坂田垂根君) ** Son of Ōtamusaka no Mikoto. == See Also == * {{ill|List of Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|国造の一覧|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/List of Kuni no Miyatsuko|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 国造}}
== Notes ==
{{reflist}}
== References == * *Dictionary of National History* (Yoshikawa Kōbunkan) * Tarō Sakamoto and Kunio Hirano, *Dictionary of Ancient Japanese Clans and Personal Names* (Yoshikawa Kōbunkan) * *Japanese Historical Dictionary* (Yamakawa Shuppansha) * *Shintō Dictionary* (Rinsen Shoten)
